{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.testng:testng:7.0.0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7399-fails-javac-compile-org.testng-testng-7.0.0-199e2a45\n\nThe failure label was `fails-javac-compile`, and the earliest run did fail in `:compileTestJava`: `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T11-57-09-482772Z.log` shows 14 TestNG 7.0.0 API mismatches in the generated tests, including missing `org.testng.internal.annotations.Converter`, `ClassHelper.createInstance1(...)` signature changes, inaccessible `Parser.TESTNG_DTD_URL`, missing `TestNG.TEST_CLASSPATH`, and `TestResult()` no longer being public.\n\nHowever, the preserved run clearly progressed past compilation. Later logs show the remaining failures were in `:nativeTest`, with `NullPointerException` from `org.testng.internal.InstanceCreator.newInstance` / `TestNG.createExecutorFactoryInstanceUsing` and an `http` URL protocol failure in `MainTest` (`human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T12-05-35-423102Z.log`). The missing-registration trace logs also show resource gaps at `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-16-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-08T12-13-40-049109Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-17-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-08T12-13-59-632076Z.log`.\n\nThe most likely final failing stage is the automation/metrics handoff rather than the library test itself. `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` records that changing the `org.testng.internal.thread.DefaultThreadPoolExecutorFactory` metadata condition from `org.testng.internal.InstanceCreator` to `org.testng.TestNG` made `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.testng:testng:7.0.0` pass, and the last verification logs (`human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T12-24-25-069191Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T12-24-47-701608Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T12-28-49-426241Z.log`) all show `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` with `47 tests successful, 0 failed`. Despite that, `stats/org.testng/testng/7.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `iterations: 3`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no recorded artifacts.\n\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially the TestNG 7.0.0 test updates and `metadata/org.testng/testng/7.0.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.testng:testng:7.0.0` from the preserved branch with the pinned GraalVM referenced in `human-intervention-logs/org.testng:testng:7.0.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`.\n3. If that rerun is green, investigate why the run was still recorded as failed in `stats/org.testng/testng/7.0.0/execution-metrics.json` and close out the human-intervention path instead of regenerating from scratch."}}
